\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Immediate History:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 July 1 I after some mild exertion at the pool, I felt the beginning of one of my previous episodes of confusion.   \endash  more on this later}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Took 250 mg of Fluconazole, followed by 2 days of 125.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 
Immediately had polyuria, fatigue and darkened urine.  Drinking only made me pee more.  I had nausea, but continued to eat normally.  I also had confusion/mind fog.  One morning, I near fell asleep many times on the drive to work.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Over the next 10 days I lost about 12-15 pounds. It was July and 115 outside and I did not sweat, in fact I couldn\rquote t feel any temperature discomfort hot or cold\'85
I could walk around my house with little on, or cover up with many blankets and I felt the same \endash  bad.  I saw my doctor during this time, he did the Chem 16 and Urinalysis.  Everything was normal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Then the stomach cramps started.  One night it would be my lower abdomen \endash 
 severe cramping after eating.  Then, the next night it would be higher.  During all this time I had increased urine volumes.  Finally, one night I had chest pains, I had been withholding urination, but decided to totally empty my bladder.  Within 15 minu
tes of that, I felt a relaxation within my body and the chest pains disappeared.  For a short time, it felt like I was walking on wet carpet.  As if there was extra fluid in the soles of my feet.  My nose also got very red during this time.  After this, m
y doctor ordered the abdominal and chest series and referred me eventually to a GI doc.  Strangely, I remember the exact moment the stomach pains stopped because within half an hour I had the first headache.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 
Then the headaches started, intense top of my head headaches with vision changes in my right eye.  These got progressively worse each day until one evening when I found myself to be agitated and angered by anything.  I just felt rage for some reason.  I w
ould wake up in the morning with headaches and bloo
dshot eyes.  This is when I first noticed the red-faced appearance.  This is very noticeable when comparing old photos to photos of that time.  Laying down seems to aggravate the headaches but it is hard to sleep without laying down.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Let me add that I have had so many stomach related issues in the past that 1) I can eat a full meal with a nausea level of 10 on a scale of 1-10 and 2) Nausea never makes me throw up, anymore.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 In August, I thought my Nausea and stomach issues might be due to blood sugar levels,
 so I measured them for few days.  They were always low  - 72-80, even an hour after a meal.  Drinking a sugared drink could get them to 150 briefly, but then back down.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 
Since July, I had some slight pain in my fingertips, but several weeks ago, it got much worse and my fingertips turned red and blue and the backs of my hands felt like they were on fire and  even my toes began to hurt.  So, I consulted my doctor, he said 
it was likely Reynauds, and ordered the colorflow echo and nerve test.  I took 2 days worth of 125 mg Fluconazole and the majority of the symptoms disappeared immediately, although I still have some pain and redness in my fingers.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 One more odd note \endash  I have terrible allergies every summer \endash  last year I had nice dry nasal passages the whole time through early 2012.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 This may be the longest history you have ever had prepared by a patient by the time I am finished, but I want to present everything, openly and without a filter.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\insrsid539649 1995}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 
OK, now I want to go back to the start of my stomach/other issues.  Back in 1995, I was new to Tulsa, and new to a job where they supplied free drinks/water/candy.   I have always been someone that drank only as little as needed for two reasons, 1) in my 
youth I wet the bed.  As a result, I was also restricting my fluid intake in an effort to not wet the bed 2) when I was in college, I drank too much one night and attempted to \'93rehydrate\'94
 myself by drinking a lot of fluids and became confused and had to call a house brother who took me to a clinic where they processed my blood through something.  I was foggy the whole time and barely remember it, but I do remember the doctor saying that I
 might have a problem with liquids and to only drink when thirsty.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Anyway, so in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf6\insrsid539649 1995, I changed the amount I drank of pop and water \endash 
 switching to caffeine-free things and lots of water.  I began to feel achy and seemed to be urinating all the time and scheduled a visit with my doctor (new doctor to me at the time).  He thought I might have a UTI, but couldn\rquote 
t find any evidence of one but put me on an antibiotic anyway.  Soon, I started having loose bowel movements, so he put me on Donnatal.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\cf6\insrsid539649 
(At this point I need to say that in 1983, I took one tablet of phenobarbital for recreational use, and had an emergency appendectomy less than 12 hours later.  I never told the docs about the pill, but I was in the hospital for 5 days, because they could
n\rquote t figure out what was wrong with me.  During this time, the skin on certain areas of my body just dried up and peeled off.  The doctor reported my appendix was totally ulcerated \endash  I felt fine before taking the pill.)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Anyway, as it turns out, Donnatal has Phenobarbitol in it, albeit in small amounts, so you can imagine what happened next ( I didn\rquote t put these two together until 1996 or 1997) \endash 
 my stomach suddenly had ulcers.  An endoscopy at the time showed white lesions everywhere.  The GI doc (Dr. Cottril) said I had the stomach of a 60-yr old.  It felt like my stomach was on fire.  I found the only thing that made it better was \endash 
 drinking cold water.  So, I stopped eating and just drank water for several days.  Then I started getting foggy, the area of my kidneys started hurting, and finally, I stopped being able to urinate even though I continued drinking.  This was all over a w
eek or so.  Soon, I found that if I drank enough water, I could at least think, but I was super agitated and couldn\rquote t sleep.   I didn\rquote 
t realize I was putting my blood pressure through the roof.   From my readings, I think I was Hyponatremic. I remember at one point thinking how I just wanted to relax and sleep, saw that the donnatal could cause drowsiness and took 2.  Within 1 hour I ha
d a white  bowel movement and my level of pain just increased.  At the ER, they gave me some mixture of different drugs for GI flareups \endash  which once again contained Phenobarbitol \endash 
 I threw up on the way home from the ER as the pain was increasing.  During this period of increased drinking, my wife would have to tell me something 2-3 times before I would recognize what she said.  I couldn\rquote t think straight.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 
This is when I propose I developed some sort of systemic candidiasis infection.  I also had given up on doctors.  I was taking Potassium tablets to try to pee, but still drinking lots of water ( a 16 oz glass of ice water would take me 2-3 seconds to drin
k) \endash  and not eating.  as I sat on the toilet one night about 2am trying to pee (as I had no hope of sleeping), the veins in my legs, scrotum and penis convulsed \endash  I don\rquote 
t recall what other pain I had as I was so freaked out.   First one leg had the veins bulge and my penis bent at a 60 angle to one side, then very shortly later the other leg did and my penis bent the other way.  I collapsed on the floor of the bathroom, 
unable to even call for help.  Over the next couple days, I was freezing cold, sweating profusely, and my sweat would leave a rash on my body.   I did not go to the Doctor or ER right away. This was the first time I could feel my heart pounding in my ches
t \endash  it lasted the next 15 years or so until 2010.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Slowly, I began to feel more normal, and managed to eat something.  Right before leaving for Tulsa from Norman.  As I didn\rquote 
t want to wreck, I drank a lot of water so I could concentrate, but now, I was urinating profuse amounts instead of not urinating at all.  I couldn\rquote 
t even stop on the turnpike often enough and ended up filling a 1 liter bottle in my car.  When I got to Tulsa, I went straight to the ER at St. Francis.  My BP was 225/175 or something like that.  They said I was in strokesville \endash 
 but that nothing was wrong with me \endash realize I had been to the ER 2-3 times already in the last month with stomach issues.  So, they sent me home saying it was extreme anxiety and my body was in fight or flight mode.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 
After a couple more days, I went back to Norman where my mom lived.  I tried to explain it all to her.  Finally I just wanted to die.  They knew I was at the end of my rope and hid everything dangerous.  I took a single Benadryl  thinking it might help me
 sleep.  Shortly after that, my mom made me eat a full meal of chunky soup and a coke.  I\rquote 
m not sure if it was the Benadryl of the electrolytes and caffeine, but in the next hour I probably urinated 8 times and it was as if going made me need to go more \endash  the stream of urine would increase in strength the longer I peed.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 
After that, I felt 100% normal for a short time.  My mind was not fogged, I could remember things and follow conversations.  But soon, I was foggy and started drinking water again.  Finally, I asked my Mom to take me to the Laureate.  It had been suggeste
d previously when I went to the ER with the high blood pressure, and I figured I would try anything if I could just sleep \endash  as it had now been 2 weeks or more without real sleep.  My pupils were 100% dilated which the staff found interesting.  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Upon checking in, I vowed to do whatever they said \endash 
 I just wanted something to make me sleep.  So, the first meal, I just chowed down.  I ate everything I could.  Developing during the meal I had an intoxicated feeling and had to urinate  - again a lot and frequently.  After eating, I would return to my r
oom, and first I would feel hot all over and then cold all over this would repeat several times very rapidly, say 30 seconds to a minute of cold then hot.  At the end of it, I would have a yellow waxy coating on my face, hands and feet.  My nose would als
o get bright red.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Then the psychiatrist said he thought I might be bi-polar so they started me on lithium.  That was just a salt as far as I was concerned so I was ok with it.  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf6\insrsid539649 The polyuria continued \endash 
 I was not drinking excessive water during this time.  After those first three days, I felt like I was shriveling up.  I gave up on them figuring it out and asked to look through the diagnostic manual they had behind the counter.  It was indexed by sympto
ms, which made it easy to cross index polyuria with polydipsia and arrive at Diabetes and Diabetes Insipidus.  The second one sounded like what I had to me, but it didn\rquote 
t account for all the other things going on.  However, at the end of each diagnosis was a \'93Rare\'94 section.  Two after Diabetes insipidus were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\cf6\insrsid539649 
Terminal Onset Diabetes Insipidus with Candidiasis Majeure and Minor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 .  This is what I believe I have, however, I will warn you I can find nothing on it anywhere and I have searched over the years \endash 
 I work at OU-Tulsa so have complete access to many online medical sources, but I have never been able to find anything.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 Those two explained much more of what had been going on \endash 
 the stomach issues, the inability to pee followed by polyuria and the euphoria. It also said it was Terminal due to changes in bloodflow somehow.  I don\rquote 
t recall it exactly, but I think it had to do with hyponatremia, the heart or blood pressure and switching from using Sodium dilution to Potassium concentration to control urination.  There were two treatments, one which involved treating the infection an
d an ethanol drip or something like that and one where you put the patient into an accelerated state by giving a shot of adrenaline while they were dehydrated. This somehow caused a shift in brain chemistry allowing the pituitary to take over control of e
lectrolyts. As I couldn\rquote 
t do whatever the first option was, I decided to try the second one  - in the Laureate by myself.  I told them I was checking out ADA, unless they brought me 2 two liter bottles of diet coke and let me drink as much as I wanted without disturbing me.  The
y did.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 I sat down and drank about a bottle and a half \endash  holding back the urination the whole time.  Soon, I had what could only be described as the only migraine I\rquote 
ve ever had in my life.  Every little sound was like thunder and eventually I couldn\rquote t even wiggle a finger without causing myself pain in my head.  Then, it went away\'85and so did my need to urinate \endash  most notably my bowels moved.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10976062 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af37 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid539649 After that, I felt much more normal, and was able to play along well enough that we all agreed to let me go home.  I couldn\rquote 
t follow a TV show, or a conversation, but I was out and feeling better.  From there, I went to a Doctor in Norman that treated people for systemic candidiasis.  I realize in most cases, that is probably a quack diagnosis, but for me, it worked perfectly.
  He put me on digestive enzymes and Fluconazole.  After the first Fluzonazole, within 15-30 minutes I felt so different I was scared.  My heart was racing was the main difference.  I started getting headaches, and had some polyuria \endash 
 mostly during meals, but I attempted to control that by just not completely emptying my bladder, and drinking a lot of water. Interestingly, I would still get a euphoric, relaxed feeling when I would have this polyuria.  I had my first headache centered 
